sections.heading: Coroner; duties; county attorney shall perform; expenses; delegation of duties
sections.text: (1) The county attorney shall perform all of the duties enjoined by law upon the county coroner and the county attorney shall be the ex officio county coroner. The county attorney shall receive no additional fees for the

sections.heading: constitutional. Effect is to incorporate in new law the existing laws defining the duties of coroner
sections.text: State ex rel. Crosby v. Moorhead, 100 Neb. 298, 159 N.W. 412 (1916).
